cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CY

Reasoning: 

- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the communication protocols used in wireless charging standards, which involves information transmission and processing. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The proposed concept of wireless charger networking involves multiple chargers working together to facilitate information collection and control, which falls under the scope of multi-agent systems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the networking aspect of wireless charging, including the proposed wireless charger network and its application in user-charger assignment. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The proposed wireless charger network involves control and coordination of multiple chargers, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the potential benefits of the proposed wireless charger network in terms of reduced cost for users, which falls under the scope of computers and society.
